  • [800 Series LR] 800 Series Zwave Outlet extend data transmission range. Add LR via SmartStart in an 800 Series Hub. Z wave Outlet can transmit up to 1300 Ft in open areas
  • [Voice Control and Dimming] Dimmable Z -Wave plug can be adjusted to different brightness through Google Assistant and Alexa. For example, "Alexa, turn the desk lamp to 30%"
  • [S2 Security] S2 Zwave plugs have a unique matching QR code (DSK). Zwave devices use strong data encryption to ensure security between devices. And there are mechanisms to intercept attackers and replay messages
  • [Compatibility] Zwave smart plug needs to work with a hub! The Z-Wave smart plug is compatible with SmartThings, Vera, Wink, Fibaro, Homeseer, 2GIG, Hubitat and other hubs. Note: Can not connect with ECHO PLUS, Vivint Hub
  • [Z-Wave Repeater] All New One Z-Wave plugs can act as Z-Wave repeaters to transmit signals when working. Note: When the Zwave Smart Outlet acts as a repeater, it can only relay up to 4 layers of signals
  • [Mini Design] The compact design of Plug means that smart plugs can be used in a same outlet. MAX 300W

Product description

New One Z-Wave Plug 800 Series

Item Model N4012-800
Z-Wave Frequence 908.42MHz
Hub Compatibility SmartThings, Hubitat, Vera, Wink and so on.
Item size 2.99*1.46*1.02 in
Certification Z-Wave, FCC
Max Loading 300W
Input 120V 60Hz
Temperature range for use 32°F~104°F (0℃~40℃)
Z-Wave Chip 800 Series

Z-Wave Plus

Simply scan the code to connect zwave smart plug to your zwave hub.

ZWave Hub Required

Control your lights remotely with ease by pairing this device with your Z-Wave certified hub/gateway. Compatible with SmartThings, Fibaro, and more.

FCC Certified

FCC Certified, safe smart plug. The 800 Series Z-Wave Plug with S2 security. It pre-sets the program.

Compact Design

The size of the smart plug is designed to limit space and you can use 2 smart plugs at the same time in a standard outlet

  • Do I need a hub?

    Yes, you need a zwave hub first.

    Compatible with Hubitat, SmartThings, Vera, Wink, Fibaro, Homeseer, 2GIG.

    Note: Can not connect with ECHO PLUS , Vivint Hub!

  • Which lights can be used this dimming plug?

    It is compatible with dimmable LED lamps, bulbs, CFLs, halogen, incandescent, string and fluorescent lamps, Its load power must be less than 300W.

  • How to reset the smart plug?

    Press the button twice quickly holding it 10 secs on a 3rd press.

      4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good product, excellent support, not z-wave series 700
      Reviewed in the United States on July 19, 2023
      Style: Dimmer Outlet-2 Pack
      I was looking for a dimmer small enough that 2 would fit in a wall socket, at a reasonable price. Don't know the brand but this looked good so I ordered a 2-pack. They arrived promptly and paired easily - but without security - with my system (Home Assistant/Z-Wave... See more
      I was looking for a dimmer small enough that 2 would fit in a wall socket, at a reasonable price. Don't know the brand but this looked good so I ordered a 2-pack. They arrived promptly and paired easily - but without security - with my system (Home Assistant/Z-Wave JS). Turns out they would only pair at S2 level when placed within about 5 ft. of the controller. Also HA showed there was new firmware available so I contacted the seller to ask where to download it but wasn't expecting much. They actually replied within 24 hours that my version is the latest and that they'll mail me new versions. They also asked if there were any connection issues so I mentioned the pairing problem. They offered to replace the units (and I'd not have to return the old ones) which they promptly shipped and which paired securely without problems. They followed up to check that the new ones worked and also answered a question I had about settings.

      Overall a good product and excellent customer support. I am dropping 1 star because the description is "700 Series Smart Dimmer" while it's actually z-wave 500 Series.

    • Dylan Zalewski
      1.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      TL;DR: Save yourself some headache. Don't buy the cheap option.
      Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
      Style: ON/OFF Outlet-2 Pack
      I bought a 2-pack of the basic Z-Wave smart plugs (on/off only). Pairing was a breeze and they appeared to work. However, after moving these to their desired location (well within range of the hub and certainly within range of the rest of the network) they started behaving... See more
      I bought a 2-pack of the basic Z-Wave smart plugs (on/off only). Pairing was a breeze and they appeared to work. However, after moving these to their desired location (well within range of the hub and certainly within range of the rest of the network) they started behaving strangely. They had a delay of about 10-15 seconds and would randomly drop from the network. Worse still, all the other devices in my Z-Wave network began misbehaving as well. I rebooted the hub and all the devices in the network just to be safe and same thing. I unplugged these plugs and everything started behaving properly again.

      I know this is not an issue with my hub or my network (I only have about 20 devices right now, including these and they're all within range of the hub and hum along happily without these plugs). Looking at the logs on my hub it appears these plugs were the source of broadcast storms. I've since initiated a return and ordered the similar Aeotec product (a brand I know I can trust).

      Lo instalé en la habitación de mi hijo para controlar el brillo de su lámpara de mesa. Este es de los pocos dimmers donde la lámpara trabaja bien en el rango completo de intensidades.
      Lo agregué a mi red Z-Wave controlada por Home Assistant, una vez que ingresé el PIN, lo detectó inmeditamente y fué posible configurar parámetros adicionales muy fácilmente.
      Se puede controlar desde la app o localmente:
      - 1 click: enciende/apaga la carga
      - 2 clicks: activa el brillo máximo (programable)
      - mantener presionado: sube / baja gradualmente el brillo
